      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "803e09044e37f7f525b58828adaa90892a6f74d4",
            "subject": "LU-56 lnet: router-checker (RC) cleanup"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Liang Zhen",
          "email": "liang@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-05-29 06:15:39.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Liang Zhen",
          "email": "liang@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-06-05 04:10:20.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-56 lnet: parse RC ping in event callback",
        "message": "LU-56 lnet: parse RC ping in event callback\n\nIn current LNet, we don't parse router-checker ping in EQ callback,\nNI information from remote side is attached on peer and it's parsed\nfor each sending. This is OK for now but with upcoming SMP\nimprovements, the global LNET_LOCK is removed and EQ callback and\npeer/router are proteced by different locks, which means sink buffer\nof RC ping could be in progressing of change when other thread is\nreading it in lnet_send(), and get wrong information.\n\nThis patch will parse ping information in EQ callback, and store it\nin a new member lnet_route_t::lr_downis which is just a integer,\nalthough reader in lnet_send() still don't have lock while reading\nit, but it's OK because it's just an integer and reader can\natomically read reliable result even w/o any lock.\n\nIt should also be a little faster than original implememtation\nbecause we don't have to parse RC ping, which should be updated\nonce for many seconds, for each sending.\n\nSigned-off-by: Liang Zhen <liang@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I5b89fabfd22f22ba171ef63d30da2d32e2788b16\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
